  "prompt": "What are some alternatives to yelp in India?",
  "response": "In India, several alternatives to Yelp can help users find restaurants, services, and places of interest. Here are some popular options:\n\n1. **Zomato**: One of the most popular platforms in India for discovering restaurants, Zomato offers user reviews, menus, photos, and even options for food delivery.\n\n2. **Swiggy**: While primarily a food delivery app, Swiggy also allows users to explore local restaurants and read customer reviews.\n\n3. **Google Maps**: Widely used for navigation, Google Maps also provides user-generated reviews, ratings, and photos for various businesses, including restaurants and cafes.\n\n4. **Justdial**: This local search engine helps users find businesses, service providers, and restaurants. It features user ratings, reviews, and contact information.\n\n5. **Tripadvisor**: Although it caters to travelers, Tripadvisor is useful for finding restaurants and attractions, with extensive user reviews and ratings.\n\n6. **BookMyShow**: Primarily known for booking movie tickets, BookMyShow also offers restaurant suggestions and reviews, especially around entertainment venues.\n\n7. **Facebook**: Many restaurants and businesses maintain Facebook pages where customers can leave reviews and ratings.\n\n8. **Magicpin**: This app focuses on local businesses and provides discounts, deals, and user reviews, especially for restaurants and shops.\n\n9. **Dineout**: This platform specializes in restaurant reservations, offering user reviews, menus, and exclusive deals.\n\n10. **Nearbuy**: Nearbuy offers deals and discounts for restaurants, spas, and local experiences, along with user reviews.\n\nThese platforms provide a mix of reviews, ratings, and additional services, catering to various needs for discovering local businesses in India.",
